Today, the President and Vice President met with 12 Latino leaders to discuss the Build Back Better Agenda and their commitment to equity. They emphasized their promise to invest in Latino families and businesses as part of the recovery from the COVID-19 pandemic. The President and Vice President also expressed their belief in the American Dream and their dedication to strengthening democracy and protecting voting rights. They pledged to continue fighting against domestic terrorism rooted in white supremacy and hate-fueled violence, as well as addressing gun violence. Additionally, they reiterated their support for immigration reform that includes a path to citizenship for Dreamers, farm workers, TPS holders, and essential workers.